<div class="dablink">"Spear of Destiny" redirects here. For other uses, see <a href="/wiki/Spear_of_Destiny_(disambiguation)" title="Spear of Destiny (disambiguation)">Spear of Destiny (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Fra_Angelico_027.jpg" class="image" title="Jesus' side is pierced with a spear, Fra Angelico (c. 1440), Dominican monastery of San Marco, Florence."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1a/Fra_Angelico_027.jpg/180px-Fra_Angelico_027.jpg" width="180" height="180" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Fra_Angelico_027.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Jesus' side is pierced with a spear, <a href="/wiki/Fra_Angelico" title="Fra Angelico">Fra Angelico</a> (c. 1440), Dominican monastery of San Marco, <a href="/wiki/Florence" title="Florence">Florence</a>.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The <b>Holy Lance</b> (also known as the <b>Spear of Destiny</b>, <b>Holy Spear</b>, <b>Lance of Longinus</b>, <b>Spear of Longinus</b> or <b>Spear of Christ</b>) is the name given to the <a href="/wiki/Lance" title="Lance">lance</a> that pierced Jesus's side in <a href="/wiki/Gospel_of_John" title="Gospel of John">John's account</a> of the <a href="/wiki/Crucifixion_of_Jesus" title="Crucifixion of Jesus">crucifixion of Jesus</a>.</p>
